{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A request whose signature does not match its body is rejected with a 401 response; the body is not forwarded.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is at a module handoff: HTTP/body parsing + signature verifier + enqueue path. A pure unit test of HMAC compare can pass while middleware wiring still forwards invalid events. Real OS/network is not required; in-process app wiring with raw-body fixture is enough, so System is rejected.","test_description":"Run the HTTP handler in-process with real request parsing middleware and a test queue adapter. Send a request where `X-Signature-256` is computed from different bytes than the sent raw body. Assert 401 and assert no enqueue call/persisted record.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"An event is written to the persistent queue before the HTTP 200 acknowledgment is returned to the sender.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is ordering across handler and persistence module. Need real queue persistence component (e.g., local DB/file-backed queue) to catch ack-before-durable-write bugs. No external network/OS primitive beyond local module wiring is required, so System is rejected.","test_description":"Use in-process HTTP handler plus real persistent queue implementation on local test storage. Instrument write and response timestamps/hooks; assert the durable write completes before 200 is emitted.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The handler returns the HTTP response without waiting for downstream processing of the event to finish.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Bug appears in async orchestration between handler, queue, and downstream work